com.launchdarkly.client.interfaces

Interface DiagnosticDescription

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    InMemoryFeatureStore, PersistentDataStoreBuilder, RedisDataStoreBuilder, RedisFeatureStoreBuilder, TestFeatureStore

    public interface DiagnosticDescription
    Optional interface for components to describe their own configuration.

    The SDK uses a simplified JSON representation of its configuration when recording diagnostics data. Any class that implements FeatureStoreFactory, UpdateProcessorFactory, EventProcessorFactory, or PersistentDataStoreFactory may choose to contribute values to this representation, although the SDK may or may not use them. For components that do not implement this interface, the SDK may instead describe them using getClass().getSimpleName().

    The describeConfiguration(LDConfig) method should return either null or a JSON value. For custom components, the value must be a string that describes the basic nature of this component implementation (e.g. "Redis"). Built-in LaunchDarkly components may instead return a JSON object containing multiple properties specific to the LaunchDarkly diagnostic schema.

    Since:
    4.12.0
